My Meme

My motivation while creating this meme was to create a representation of myself that is true and original.

This is my meme

library(magick)

meme1 <- image_read("https://pbs.twimg.com/media/EWT0S8NUcAEUBSz.png") %>% #top image
  image_scale(300)

meme2 <- image_read("https://i.pinimg.com/originals/4a/de/cf/4adecfe986ba6ccbd6c970d167c0a679.jpg") %>% #bottom image
  image_scale(300) %>%
  image_crop("0x430")

meme_text1 <- image_blank(width = 300, 
                         height = 169,
                         color = "#eeeee4") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Me before my nap:",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 35,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

meme_text2 <- image_blank(width = 300,
                          height = 430,
                          color = "#eeeee4") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Me after my nap:",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 35,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")
 
row1 <- c(meme_text1, meme1)%>%
  image_append()

row2 <- c(meme_text2, meme2)%>%
  image_append()

meme <- c(row1, row2) %>% #concatenating the 1st and 2nd set of meme and text together
  image_append(stack = TRUE) #stacks the meme
image_write(meme,"my_meme.png")

image_crop(meme, "200x200")
image_border (meme, "#000000", "20x20")

My animated GIF

My motivation and creative mindset for this GIF was thinking about people who make me happy, so I created a GIF just for that.

This is my GIF

library(magick)

words <- c("You", "Make", "Me", "Happy!") #character vector

smiley_face <- image_read("https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Mr._Smiley_Face.svg/1200px-Mr._Smiley_Face.svg.png") %>% #first image
  image_scale(260) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

finger <- image_read("https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2013/07/12/16/52/you-151415_1280.png") %>% #last image
  image_scale(300) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

frame1 <- finger %>% #first frame
  image_annotate(text = words[1], size = 100, 
                 font = "Impact", 
                 gravity = "north" ) %>%
  image_scale(400) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

frame2 <- image_blank(width = 240, height = 100) %>% #second frame
  image_annotate(text = words[2], 
                 size = 100, 
                 font = "Impact", 
                 gravity = "center" ) %>%
  image_scale(200) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")
  
frame3 <- image_blank(width = 140, height = 100) %>% #third frame
  image_annotate(text = words[3], 
                 size = 100, 
                 font = "Impact", 
                 gravity = "center" ) %>%
  image_scale(200) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

frame4 <- smiley_face %>% #fourth frame
  image_annotate(text = words[4], 
                 size = 100, 
                 font = "Impact", 
                 gravity = "north" ) %>%
  image_scale(400) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

animation <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4) #concatenating all frames together
image_write(animation,"my_animation.gif")

image_animate(animation, fps = 2) #executing code in 2 fps
